### DO NOT
- Change the public API of `RuntimeProjection` (keep `from_file` and `for_run`)
- Change the `Result` type alias — it uses `crate::effect_driver::Result` which is
  `Box<dyn std::error::Error + Send + Sync>` and is fine to keep
- Remove existing test cases — extend them or add new ones
- Import RuntimeEvent directly into projection.rs — the projection reads JSONL, not
  RuntimeEvent values; it works off string kind labels from the log

### Existing Code Context

`crates/roko-runtime/src/projection.rs` — current `RunSummary` fields (lines 12-33):
```rust
pub struct RunSummary {
    pub run_id: String,
    pub template: Option<String>,
    pub prompt: Option<String>,
    pub current_phase: Option<String>,
    pub phases_visited: Vec<String>,
    pub gates_passed: Vec<String>,
    pub gates_failed: Vec<String>,
    pub agents_spawned: u32,
    pub is_complete: bool,
